article.headline: Elias Ralph, Lamar Washington lead Pacific to 80-67 victory over San Jose State at Rainbow Classic
article.description: — Elias Ralph and Lamar Washington scored 14 points apiece as Pacific beat San Jose State 80-67 on Friday night at the Rainbow Classic.
article.linkText: Elias Ralph, Lamar Washington lead Pacific to 80-67 victory over San Jose State at Rainbow Classic
article.story: HONOLULU -- — Elias Ralph and Lamar Washington scored 14 points apiece as Pacific beat San Jose State 80-67 on Friday night at the Rainbow Classic. Ralph also had 10 rebounds for the Tigers (2-0). Washington added 10 assists and seven rebounds. Elijah Fisher shot 4 of 6 from the field and 5 of 6 from the free-throw line to finish with 13 points. Josh Uduje finished with 15 points for the Spartans (0-2). Will McClendon had 14 points and Robert Vaihola scored 12. Pacific took the lead with 15:27 remaining in the first half and never looked back. Jefferson Koulibaly led his team in scoring with 11 points in the first half to help put them up 38-29 at the break. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
